{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.22",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 22 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:1",
      "text": "A fair name is better than much wealth, and good favour is above silver and gold.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:2",
      "text": "The rich and the poor meet together; but the Lord made them both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:3",
      "text": "An intelligent man seeing a bad man severely punished is himself instructed, but fools pass by and are punished. `off-scouring;' perhaps `ransom,' q. d. that which cleans.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:4",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is the offspring of wisdom, and wealth, and glory, and life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:5",
      "text": "Thistles and snares are in perverse ways; but he that keeps his soul will refrain from them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:7",
      "text": "The rich will rule over the poor, and servants will lend to their own masters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:8",
      "text": "He that sows wickedness shall reap troubles; and shall fully receive the punishment of his deeds. 8a God loves a cheerful and liberal man; but a man shall fully prove the folly of his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:9",
      "text": "He that has pity on the poor shall himself be maintained; for he has given of his own bread to the poor. 9a He that gives liberally secures victory and honour; but he takes away the life of them that possess them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:10",
      "text": "Cast out a pestilent person from the council, and strife shall go out with him; for when he sits in the council he dishonours all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:11",
      "text": "The Lord loves holy hearts, and all blameless persons are acceptable with him: a king rules with his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:12",
      "text": "But the eyes of the Lord preserve discretion; but the transgressor despises wise words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:13",
      "text": "The sluggard makes excuses, and says, There is a lion in the ways, and murderers in the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:14",
      "text": "The mouth of a transgressor is a deep pit; and he that is hated of the Lord shall fall into it. 14a Evil ways are before a man, and he does not like to turn away from them; but it is needful to turn aside from a perverse and bad way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:15",
      "text": "Folly is attached to the heart of a child, but the rod and instruction are then far from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:16",
      "text": "He that oppresses the poor, increases his own substance, yet gives to the rich so as to make it less.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:17",
      "text": "Incline thine ear to the words of wise men: hear also my word, and apply thine heart,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:18",
      "text": "that thou mayest know that they are good: and if thou lay them to heart, they shall also gladden thee on thy lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:19",
      "text": "That thy hope may be in the Lord, and he may make thy way known to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:20",
      "text": "And do thou too repeatedly record them for thyself on the table of thine heart, for counsel and knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:21",
      "text": "I therefore teach thee truth, and knowledge good to hear; that thou mayest answer words of truth to them that question thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:22",
      "text": "Do no violence to the poor, for he is needy: neither dishonour the helpless man in the gates.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:23",
      "text": "For the Lord will plead his cause, and thou shalt deliver thy soul in safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:24",
      "text": "Be not companion to a furious man; neither lodge with a passionate man:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:25",
      "text": "lest thou learn of his ways, and get snares to thy soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:26",
      "text": "Become not surety from respect of a man's person.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:27",
      "text": "For if those have not whence to give compensation, they will take the bed that is under thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:28",
      "text": "Remove not the old landmarks, which thy fathers placed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.22.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 22:29",
      "text": "It is fit that an observant man and one diligent in his business should attend on kings, and not attend on slothful men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
